Russia Central Bank Sees No Threat From U.S. Cut, RIA Reports

-- B y   L y u b o v   P r o n i n a
-- 
2011-08-06T13:24:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-06/russia-central-bank-sees-no-threat-from-u-s-cut-ria-reports.html
Standard & Poor’s  downgrade of the
U.S.’s AAA credit rating will not affect the stability of the
Russian economy or lead to a change in its foreign currency
reserves in the short-term, RIA Novosti reported today, citing
Sergey Shvetsov, deputy chairman at Bank Rossii.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lyubov Pronina in Moscow at 
